---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Contact - LocalResizer" description="Get in touch with the LocalResizer team.">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 prose prose-slate">
    <h1>Contact Us</h1>
    <p>Have feedback, feature ideas, or bug reports? We would love to hear from you.</p>
    <h2>Email</h2>
    <p>Reach us at <a href="mailto:support@localresizer.com">support@localresizer.com</a>.</p>
    <p>We currently route this address through Cloudflare Email Routing so the support inbox is active while the site is still in its early stage.</p>
    <h2>What to Contact Us About</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Bug reports for the live homepage tool or current published pages</li>
      <li>Questions about current format support or workflow limits</li>
      <li>Feature requests that fit the current privacy-first, browser-based direction</li>
      <li>Business, partnership, or general site inquiries</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>When Reporting a Bug</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The page URL where the issue happened</li>
      <li>Your browser and version</li>
      <li>The type of file you were working with, such as JPEG, PNG, or WebP</li>
      <li>Whether you were using a target-size page or an exact canvas page</li>
      <li>A short description of what you expected and what actually happened</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>What Helps Us Respond Faster</h2>
    <p>The most useful bug reports are concrete and reproducible. If you can include the target page, the file format, the exact limit you were aiming for, and what result you got instead, it is much easier for us to investigate the issue and decide whether it is a bug, a product gap, or an expected best-effort limit.</p>
    <h2>Current Scope</h2>
    <p>The current public workflow is focused on static image compression and resizing for JPEG, PNG, and WebP files.</p>
    <p>The live public pages currently cover homepage quick tools, target-size pages, and exact YouTube banner or thumbnail canvas pages.</p>
    <h2>Current Stage</h2>
    <p>LocalResizer is still intentionally focused. We would rather keep the live scope narrow and accurate than publish unsupported workflows too early.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
